# Git & Documentation Standards

## Git Workflow

- Use conventional commit messages (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)
- Create feature branches for new functionality
- Test changes thoroughly before committing
- Update version number in manifest.json for releases

## Documentation Requirements

- Keep README.md updated with installation and usage instructions
- Document any new features or breaking changes
- Include screenshots for UI changes
- Maintain clear contributing guidelines

## Commit Message Examples

- `feat: Add new popup animation`
- `fix: Correctly parse domain names`
- `docs: Update installation instructions`
- `style: Improve dark mode colors`

## Version Management

- Update version in manifest.json for releases
- Use semantic versioning (major.minor.patch)
- Document breaking changes in commit messages

## Pull Request Guidelines

- Write clear descriptions of changes
- Link related issues (e.g., "Fixes #123")
- Test changes in Chrome developer mode
- Ensure compatibility with existing storage format
